PHP Syntax

1. PHP Tags

    PHP code is written inside special tags:
    -----
    <?php
    // PHP code goes here
    ?>
    -----
    Short tags (<? ?>) are discouraged; always use full <?php ?>.

2. Statements

    Each PHP statement ends with a semicolon ;.
    -----
    $name = "John";
    echo $name;

3. Comments

    Single-line comment:
    -----
    // This is a comment
    # Another single-line comment
    -----

    Multi-line comment:
    -----
    /*
    This is a multi-line comment
    */

4. Output

    To print something:
    -----
    echo "Hello, world!";
    print "Welcome!";

5. Variables

    Start with $
    -----
    $age = 25;

6. Case Sensitivity

    Variable names are case-sensitive:
    -----
    $name = "Alice";
    echo $Name; // This will cause an error
    -----

    Function names and keywords are not case-sensitive:
    -----
    ECHO "Hello"; // Works fine